  "dcterms:abstract": "Bioenergetic failure and oxidative stress are common pathological hallmarks of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS), but whether these could be targeted effectively for novel therapeutic interventions needs to be determined. We present evidence that inhibition of Drp1/Fis1 interaction can be an attractive target in the treatment of ALS patients.",
